{{Infobox Christian leader | honorific-prefix = {{pre-nominal styles|MRevd}} | name = Pierre Chébly | honorific-suffix = | title = Archeparch | image = | church = [[Catholic Church]] | province = | diocese = [[Maronite Catholic Archeparchy of Beirut]] | enthroned = | term-end = | term = | predecessor = | successor = | ordination = | consecration = | other_post = <!---------- Personal details ----------> | birth_name = Pierre Chébly | birth_date = | birth_place = | nationality = | religion = [[Maronite Church]] | residence = | parents = | spouse = | children = | profession = | alma_mater = | coat_of_arms = | motto = | awards = | signature = }} '''Pierre Chébly''' (19 December 1870 in Defoun, [[Lebanon]] &ndash; 30 May 1917) was an archeparch of the [[Maronite Catholic Archeparchy of Beirut]].
==Life==
Pierre Scebli was born in Defoun, [[Lebanon]]. He was ordained to the priesthood on July 14, 1897, and appointed Archbishop of Beirut on 14 February 1908, aged 36. He was consecrated bishop the following day by [[List of Maronite Patriarchs|Maronite Patriarch of Antioch]], [[Elias Peter Hoayek]]. On May 30, 1917, he died in Beirut, aged 46, after nine years as Archeparch of Beirut.<ref>[http://www.gcatholic.org/dioceses/diocese/beir3.htm gcatholic.org]</ref>
