{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2014}} {{For|the film starring Robin Williams|Cadillac Man}} '''The Cadillac Man''' is the pen name of a [[homeless]] [[white American]] writer who lived under the railroad [[viaduct]] in [[Astoria, Queens]], New York City. His book, '' Land of the Lost Souls: My Life on the Streets'' describes his experiences living on the streets.<ref>{{cite web|title=Land of the Lost Souls: My Life on the Streets|url=https://www.publishersweekly.com/978-1-59691-406-3|website=Publishers Weekly|date=March 16, 2009}}</ref> His notebooks have been excerpted in ''[[Esquire Magazine]]'',<ref>{{cite web|title=The Story of Cadillac Man and the Land of the Lost Souls|url=https://www.esquire.com/ESQ0505HOMELESSB&W_134/|website=Esquire|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090905024139/https://www.esquire.com/ESQ0505HOMELESSB%26W_134/|archivedate=September 5, 2009|date=March 11, 2009|deadurl=yes|df=mdy-all}}</ref> and his writings on street life have appeared in ''[[The New York Times]]''.<ref name="Sweeping Him Off His Street">{{cite web|last1=Cowan|first1=Coleman|title=Sweeping Him Off His Street|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2007/03/18/nyregion/thecity/18cad2.html|website=The New York Times|date=March 18, 2007}}</ref> A 2006 documentary about him<ref>[http://www.hellskitchenfilms.com/ Cadillac Man: Life Under the Viaduct] Hells Kitchen Films, 2006.</ref> has appeared in 14 film festivals.<ref name="Sweeping Him Off His Street" /> In December, 2015, he moved into an apartment in Astoria.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Parry|first1=Bill|title=Famous homeless veteran gets a home in Astoria|url=https://www.timesledger.com/stories/2015/50/cadillacman_2015_12_11_q.html/|website=Times Ledger|date=December 10, 2015}}</ref>
==Nickname== Cadillac Man does not publicly state his name,<ref name="Sweeping Him Off His Street" /> but says his nickname comes from being hit by [[Cadillac]] cars on different occasions in 1994.<ref name="Sweeping Him Off His Street"></ref>
